<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
This species is somewhat uncommon in shallower waters; it is found mostly in crevices and in rocky outcrops, mostly in clustered distributions. Juvenile specimens are somewhat similar to the juvenile specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Polyplacophora" family="Chitonidae" genus="Chiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chiton cumingsii" order="Chitonida" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cumingsii">Chiton cumingsii</taxonomicName>
differing in the paler coloration (of various shades of green), the granulation on the valves and in the overall wider body. It has been reported that this species feeds on barnacle cyprids (
<bibRefCitation author="Moreno, CA" journalOrPublisher="Oikos" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="73 - 76" title="The role of grazers in the zonation of intertidal macroalgae of the Chilean coast." url="10.2307/3544348" volume="41" year="1983">Moreno and Jaramillo 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Aguilera, MA" journalOrPublisher="Investigaciones Marinas" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="109 - 113" title="Barnacles in the diet of the molluscan grazer Chitongranosus (Frembly, 1827) present on the intertidal rockys shore of Iquique, northern de Chile." volume="33" year="2005">Aguilera 2005</bibRefCitation>
) and is preyed on by the common gull 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Laridae" genus="Larus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Larus dominicanus" order="Charadriiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dominicanus">Larus dominicanus</taxonomicName>
(Lichtenstein, 1823). It was observed also that some specimens had barnacles on the valves. This species is a physiological omnivore, having the digestive flexibility and enzymatic capacity to digest and assimilate animal preys (
<bibRefCitation author="Camus, PA" journalOrPublisher="Latin American Journal of Aquatic Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="191 - 197" title="Consumption and digestion of animal food by rocky intertidal herbivores: An evaluation of digestive flexibility and omnivory in three grazer species." url="10.3856/vol37-issue2-fulltext-6" volume="37" year="2009">Camus et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and it is also a commercially important species (
<bibRefCitation author="Osorio, C" journalOrPublisher="Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" title="Moluscos marinos en Chile: especies de importancia economica: Guia para su identificacion" year="2002">Osorio 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
